          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1634048631321-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, reboil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> chestnut mushrooms</strong> roughly</p><p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>beef mince</strong> to the pan with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong></p><p>Increase the heat to medium-high and cook for 3-4 min or until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
