    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and peel your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> then chop into batons</p><p>Wipe the reserved pan clean and return it to a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>butter </strong>with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>carrot batons</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until softened with a slight bite</p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley </strong>roughly</p>",
